properties.description:
# Cisco Secure Endpoint Exclusion List Export Workflow
The Workflow will list exclusion lists of Cisco Secure Endpoint for validating and review.
The Exclusion API in Cisco Secure Endpoint avaialble on API [v3](https://developer.cisco.com/docs/secure-endpoint/introduction/)

The Workflow work together with sub workflow (Atomics) "XDR - Automated - Generate Access Token" that you need to import after import the workflow.
The exclusion information will list and update into environment table "CiscoSecureEndpoint_Exclusion_Table" in variable.

properties.script:
import sys

accessToken = sys.argv[1]
hasToken = True if len(accessToken) > 0 else False

headerName = 'Authorization'
headerValue = 'Bearer ' + accessToken

if not hasToken:
  headerName = ''
  headerValue = ''

properties.script:
import json
import sys

# Parse the JSON string into a Python dictionary
json_data = json.loads(sys.argv[1])
# List to hold all the flattened data
flattened_data = []

# Loop through each item in 'data'
for item in json_data['data']:
    # Start with a flat dictionary containing 'guid' and 'exclusionType'
    flat_item = {
        "guid": item.get('guid', ''),
        "operatingSystem": item.get('operatingSystem', '')
    }
    
    # Flatten 'engineSettings' if it exists
    if 'properties' in item and isinstance(item['properties'], dict):
        for prop_key, prop_value in item['properties'].items():
            flat_item[f"properties_{prop_key}"] = prop_value
    
    # Add the flat_item to the list of flattened data
    flattened_data.append(flat_item)

# Now flattened_data contains the list with all data at the same level
# You can now use flattened_data as needed in your code, for example:
#print(json.dumps(flattened_data, indent=2))
flattened_data = json.dumps(flattened_data)
